---
import CollectionLayout from '../../layouts/CollectionLayout.astro';
import { fetchProducts, getCategoryProducts } from '../../data/products';

const allProducts = await fetchProducts();
const products = getCategoryProducts(allProducts, 'pendants');
---

<CollectionLayout
  title="Meteorite Pendants"
  metaTitle="Meteorite Pendants & Necklaces | Jewelry by Johan"
  description="Handcrafted Gibeon meteorite pendants and necklaces. Meteorite slice pendants, geometric forms, and custom designs with authentic Widmanstätten patterns. USA made."
  heading="Meteorite Pendants"
  subheading="Wear a slice of the cosmos around your neck — meteorite pendants hand-cut from authentic Gibeon iron, etched to reveal the ancient crystal structure within."
  products={products}
  category="Pendants Collection"
>
  <section slot="editorial" class="collection-editorial">
    <div class="editorial-inner">
      <div class="editorial-divider"></div>
      <div class="editorial-grid">
        <div>
          <p>A meteorite pendant brings 4.5 billion years of cosmic history to one of the most personal pieces of jewelry a person can wear. Gibeon meteorite pendants are typically cut as polished slices — thin cross-sections through the iron mass that expose the full width of the Widmanstätten crystal pattern in a single plane. The result looks almost architectural: geometric bands of kamacite and taenite crystal arranged in patterns that formed before Earth existed.</p>
          <p>Each pendant is crafted by hand in the Jewelry by Johan workshop in Minneapolis, with meteorite slices selected for strong pattern expression and minimal inclusions. Pendants are available in a range of sizes and forms, paired with different chain lengths and metal settings depending on the design. Every piece of Gibeon used is from pre-2004 inventory — legally acquired before Namibia's national monument designation closed new collection.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>The <strong>Stardust collection</strong> offers a distinct alternative for those who want meteorite's cosmic character in a hypoallergenic format: genuine meteorite pieces and shavings are suspended in resin and set into the pendant face, creating a jewel-like expression of the same material. Both approaches use authentic Gibeon meteorite — the difference is form, not authenticity.</p>
          <p>Gibeon meteorite is iron-based and requires proper sealing for daily wear. All Johan meteorite pendants are sealed at the workshop and backed by the same lifetime cleaning and re-etching service that covers every other piece in the collection. Orders and customization are handled on <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jewelry by Johan</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</CollectionLayout>